          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <img src="images/part1.png " alt="" style="object-fit: cover" />
          <p>
            This part of the constitution deals with the formation, renaming,
            merging, and alteration of the boundaries or names of the states and
            union territories.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="part part2">
        <div class="left">
          <h1>Part-II <br />CitizenShip</h1>
          <div class="options">
            <a href="/theory/2" method="GET"><h3>Theory</h3></a>
            <h3>Practice Now</h3>
           <a href="/partquiz/2" method="GET "><h3>Quiz</h3></a>
            <h3>Progress</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <img src="images/part2.png " alt="" />
          <p>
            This part provides for the acquisition and termination of Indian
            citizenship. It also lays down the criteria for the eligibility and
            disqualification of citizens.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="part part3">
        <div class="left">
          <h1>Part-III <br />Fundamental Rights</h1>
          <div class="options">
            <a href="/theory/3" method="GET"><h3>Theory</h3></a>
            <h3>Practice Now</h3>
            <a href="/partquiz/3" method="GET "><h3>Quiz</h3></a>
            <h3>Progress</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <img src="images/part3.png " alt="" />
          <p>
            Fundamental Rights are the basic human rights guaranteed by the
            constitution to all individuals. These rights are considered
            essential for the overall development of individuals.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="part part4">
        <div class="left">
          <h1>Part-IV <br />Directive principles of state policy</h1>
          <div class="options">
